<item>
            <title>[LU-8259] ldiskfs osd proc interface lacks __user qualifiers</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8259</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;All *_seq_write functions in lustre/osd-ldiskfs/osd_lproc.c declare&lt;br/&gt;
buffesr as &quot;const char *buffer&quot; and should use &quot;const char __user *buffer&quot; instead.&lt;br/&gt;
This includes:&lt;br/&gt;
osd_brw_stats_seq_write&lt;br/&gt;
ldiskfs_osd_cache_seq_write&lt;br/&gt;
ldiskfs_osd_wcache_seq_write&lt;br/&gt;
lprocfs_osd_force_sync_seq_write&lt;br/&gt;
ldiskfs_osd_pdo_seq_write&lt;br/&gt;
ldiskfs_osd_auto_scrub_seq_write&lt;br/&gt;
ldiskfs_osd_full_scrub_ratio_seq_write&lt;br/&gt;
ldiskfs_osd_full_scrub_threshold_rate_seq_write&lt;br/&gt;
ldiskfs_osd_track_declares_assert_seq_write&lt;br/&gt;
ldiskfs_osd_readcache_seq_write&lt;br/&gt;
ldiskfs_osd_index_in_idif_seq_write&lt;/p&gt;</description>
